    <mads:note  type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Domitius Marsus, poet of epigrams, Writer of epigrams
        a contemporary of Ovid (Pont. 4,16,5), probably to be identified with the addressee of a letter from Apollodorus, 
        teacher of rhetoric to Augustus.....Martial's frequent naming of him....gives us an idea of D.'s significance for 
        the art of the literary epigram in Rome..." Schmidt, Peter L. (Konstanz). Domitius." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity 
        volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2009. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 16 September 2009</mads:note>
